Global Caprolactone Market Insights
Caprolactone Market size was valued at USD 1.8 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 3.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Caprolactone Market Overview
The global Caprolactone market was valued at approximately USD 1.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 2.2 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.5% during the forecast period. Caprolactone, a versatile chemical used in the production of polymers, coatings, and specialty materials, is experiencing a surge in demand due to its wide applications across industries such as automotive, pharmaceuticals, and consumer goods. The increasing trend towards biodegradable plastics and eco-friendly materials is further accelerating market growth. The Asia-Pacific region, particularly China and India, is expected to witness the highest growth due to rapid industrialization and a rising demand for sustainable solutions.

